  },
  "concepts": [
    "Es = is (third person singular of ser)",
    "Un = a/an (masculine), Una = a/an (feminine)",
    "Word order is flexible: 'Es un libro' = 'It is a book'",
    "You can ask: ¿Qué es? = What is it?"
  ],
  "verbs": [
    {
      "spanish": "ser",
      "english": "to be",
      "forms": ["es"],
      "note": "es = he/she/it is"
    }
